HEADWORD: Masticin
<hw>Mas"ti*cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white, amorphous, tenacious substance resembling caoutchouc, and
obtained as an insoluble residue of mastic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

